postcontent: Colt King Cobra with the Stainless Finish and the 6” barrel. It is the EDT Model which stands for Enhanced Drilled & Tapped. This model came from Colt with the recessed barrel and drilled and tapped. Comes with the Original Factory Labeled Colt Blue Box, hangtag and paperwork. This piece is in EXTRAORDINARY LIKE NEW CONDITION with no signs of being consumer use that we can see. Please review the pictures for the extraordinary condition of this beautiful King Cobra. Very hard to improve on the condition of this Colt. The condition states it is Like New Condition with no signs of ever being "used" in any way that we can see. This King Cobra EDT is about as new condition as you can find one without actually stepping back in 1998 and buying straight from the gun shop. These Colt King Cobra Models are becoming one of the most sought after and collected model of the Colt Snake guns series simply because Colt didn't produce them but for a limited period of time and not to mention that this one is the EDT Mode. title: For Sale/Trade:  Postwar Czech K98 Mauser
postcontent: Up for sale/trade is a post-WW2 Czech K98k Mauser, chambered in 7.92x57mm (aka 8mm Mauser).  During WW2, Czechoslovakia was occupied by the Germans, who forced the famous CZ Brno arms factory to produce K98k Mauser rifles to arm the Wehrmacht.  After the end of the war, the Czechs continued to produce K98k rifles for a few more years, to rearm the Czechoslovakian military.This is an very nice condition example of a Czech K98k produced at the CZ Brno factory immediately after WW2.  Great condition metal.  Very good wood, with a handful of the usual small handling marks typical of 70 year old rifle stocks.  Bright, shiny bore.  Matching serial numbers.  Blank receiver ring (no date or factory code).  Czech lion proof marks and CZ Brno factory marking on the left side of the receiver.Price is $600 cash, or trade for one of the items below (+/- cash as needed).  I'm in South Springdale, but can meet elsewhere in NWA for the right deal.  Feel free to email me through the Armslist contact form, or text me at four 7 nine - two 8 three - three 7 7 nine.
